Sentencas: Reactive magnetron sputtering was used for deposition of thin Gd-doped ceria (GDC) films on porous NiO-YSZ (nickel oxide-yttria stabilized zirconia) substrates.
Titulo: Magnetron Sputtering of Gadolinium-doped Ceria Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction and scanning electron microscopy were used to study the effect of cathode peak power density on 5-7 mu m-thick film's microstructure and surface morphology.
Titulo: Magnetron Sputtering of Gadolinium-doped Ceria Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: It was shown that peak power density (changed from 52 to 490 W/cm(2)) has an effect on the crystallite size, microstrains and texture coefficient of the GDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Magnetron Sputtering of Gadolinium-doped Ceria Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Increasing peak power density suppresses the columnar structure of deposited films and leads to formation of more continuous and denser films.
Titulo: Magnetron Sputtering of Gadolinium-doped Ceria Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: As a result, anode-supported single cells with sputtered at room temperature GDC electrolyte were fabricated and demonstrated maximum power density of 1.07 W/cm(2) at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Magnetron Sputtering of Gadolinium-doped Ceria Electrolyte for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
